Combining Special Missing with Informat and Format Statements for Great Reports

Caroline Ledbetter, MPH

Writing/Reading

Special Missings
-Any value from A-Z + _ (not case sensitive)

Informats
-Used to read values in

Formats
-Keeps underlying structure/makes pretty output

Set Formats First

/* Set up formats invalue for informats and value for formats*/
PROC FORMAT;
/* you can use .any letter for special missing*/
    INVALUE RDK1D   7 = .R
                    9 = .D
                    OTHER = _SAME_;
    INVALUE URDK    3 = .U
                    7 = .R
                    9 = .D
                    OTHER = _SAME_;
    INVALUE RDK2D   77 = .R
                    99 = .D
                    OTHER = _SAME_;
    INVALUE TF      'TRUE' = 1
                    'FALSE' = 0;
    INVALUE NA      'NA' = .
                    OTHER = [8.];
    VALUE EDUCADULT 1 = 'Less Than 9th Grade'
                    2 = '9-11th Grade/No Diploma'
                    3 = 'High School Grad/GED or Equivalent'
                    4 = 'Some College or AA degree'
                    5 = 'College Graduate or above'
                    .R = 'Refused Answer'
                    .D = "Don't Know";
/* you can then use formats to display labels for special missings */
    VALUE BMI       2 = 'Normal'
                    3 - 4 = 'Overweight/Obese'
                    .M = 'Missing'
                    .U = 'Underweight'
                    .R = 'Refused Answer'
                    .D = "Don't Know";
    VALUE YNTWO     1 = 'Yes'
                    2 = 'No'
                    .R = 'Refused Answer'
                    .D = "Don't Know";
    VALUE SLQWK     0 = 'Never'
                    1 = 'Rarely (1-2 nights/week)'
                    2 = 'Occasionally (3-4 nights/week)'
                    3 = 'Frequently (5 or 4 more nights/week)'
                    .R = 'Refused Answer'
                    .D = "Don't Know"
;
RUN;

Reading In Data

/* using informats in a data infile statement */
DATA DPDRQ.DRX (DROP = VAR1);
    INFILE "P:\CBC\Shared\Projects\P1229PerkinsCoie/DataProcessed/DRQ/DRXSEQN.csv" FIRSTOBS = 2 DSD;
    INFORMAT SEQN 8. CEREAL TF. HISGRWGT TF. HISGRCAL TF. DRXIGRMS NA. DRXISUGR NA. ;
    INPUT VAR1 SEQN CEREAL HISGRWGT HISGRCAL DRXIGRMS DRXISUGR;
    FORMAT CEREAL HISGRWGT HISGRCAL YNO.;
RUN;

/* if your data is already in a sas data frame you can use input and your 
   informat statement */
DATA DPDRQ.ALL;
    SET DPDRQ.ALL;
    ARRAY RDK1D (33) BPQ050A BPQ090D BPQ100D DIQ010 DIQ050 DIQ070 DIQ160 DMDEDUC2 SLQ030--SLQ240;
    ARRAY RDK2D (4) INDFMINC DMDEDUC3 SLD010H SLD020M;
    DO i = 1 to 33;
        RDK1D(i) = INPUT(RDK1D(i), RDK1D.);
    END;
    DO i = 1 to 4;
        RDK2D(i) = INPUT(RDK2D(i), RDK2D.);
    END;
/* Use format to control how it looks in reports */
    FORMAT DMDEDUC3 EDUCCHILD.
           BPQ050A BPQ090D BPQ100D DIQ050 DIQ070 DIQ160 PAQ620 PAQ665 PAD320 SLQ050 SLQ060 YNTWO.
           DIQ010 DIAB.
           INDFMINC ANNFINC.
           DMDEDUC2 EDUCADULT.
           RIAGENDR GENDER.
           RIDRETH1 RACEETH.
           RIDEXPRG PREG.
           SLQ030 SLQ040 SLQWK.
           SLQ080--SLQ160 SLQMO.
           SLQ170--SLQ240 SLQDIFF.
           PA YNO.
           SDDSRVYR SDDSRVYR.;
    IF WTDRD1 = . AND WTSAF2YR = . THEN DELETE;
    DROP i;
    LABEL DRXIGRMS = "Total Grams of Cereal Reported from 2 day DRQ"
          DRXISUGR = "Total Grams of Sugar From Cereal Reported from 2 day DRQ"
          HISGRWGT = 'Consumed Cereal w/ more than 17% sugar by weight'
          HISGRCAL = 'Consumed Cereal w/ more than 15% sugar by calories';
RUN;

PROC FREQ


/* Proc Freq with missing printed but not included in cumulative totals */
PROC FREQ DATA = DPDRQ.ANALYSIS; 
    TABLE DMDEDUC2 SLQ030--SLQ040 BMICAT PAD320 WAISTCM /MISSPRINT;
RUN;

/* Missing included in cumulative totals */
PROC FREQ DATA = DPDRQ.ANALYSIS; 
    TABLE DMDEDUC2 SLQ030--SLQ040 BMICAT PAD320 WAISTCM /MISSING;
RUN;

/* Missing not printed (Default) */
PROC FREQ DATA = DPDRQ.ANALYSIS; 
    TABLE DMDEDUC2 SLQ030--SLQ040 BMICAT PAD320 WAISTCM;
RUN;

THE CODE

/* Put currently loaded formats in a data table */
PROC FORMAT FMTLIB OUT = FORMATS;
RUN;

/* Get variable names from proc contents into a data table */
ODS OUTPUT VARIABLES = VARIABLES;
PROC CONTENTS DATA = DPDRQ.ANALYSIS;
RUN;
ODS OUTPUT CLOSE;

/* select only user defined formats from formats data table 
   concatenate the start value to it's label  (formats have type N, 
   informats have type I)*/
DATA TMP (KEEP = FMTNAME VALUE);
    SET FORMATS;
    IF TYPE NE 'N' THEN DELETE;
    VALUE = CATX(' = ', START, LABEL);
    IF START NE END 
        THEN VALUE = CATX(' = ', CATX(' - ', START, END), LABEL);
RUN;

/* paste all the values together with a newline seperator between */
DATA FM (DROP = FMT_OLD);
    SET TMP (RENAME = (VALUE = FMT_OLD));
    BY FMTNAME;
    RETAIN VALUE;
    LENGTH VALUE $ 2000;
    IF FIRST.FMTNAME THEN VALUE = "";
    VALUE = CATX(' ~n ', VALUE, FMT_OLD);
    IF LAST.FMTNAME THEN OUTPUT;
RUN;


/* Drop everything from the "." on (Formats have a period at the end)*/
DATA VARIABLES;
    SET VARIABLES;
    FORMAT = COMPRESS(FORMAT, '.');
RUN;

/* merge the variable number, name, label, and formates */
PROC SQL;
    CREATE TABLE DATADIC AS
    SELECT V.NUM, V.VARIABLE, V.TYPE, V.LABEL, FM.FMTNAME, FM.VALUE
    FROM VARIABLES AS V LEFT JOIN FM AS FM
    ON V.FORMAT = FM.FMTNAME
;
QUIT;

/* put the variables in order by number*/
PROC SORT DATA = DATADIC;
    BY NUM;
RUN;

/*out put to a pdf file*/
ODS PDF FILE = 'P:\CBC\Shared\Projects\P1229PerkinsCoie\Background\DATADICTIONARY.PDF';
ODS ESCAPECHAR = '~';
PROC PRINT DATA = DATADIC NOOBS;
RUN;
PROC PRINT DATA = DATADIC2 NOOBS;
RUN;
ODS PDF CLOSE;
